 20     /**
 21      * A prototype for Analyzers objects.
 22      * @constructor
 23      */
 24     fullproof.AbstractAnalyzer = function() {
 25         /**
 26          * Sometimes it's convenient to receive the whole set of words cut and normalized by the
 27          * analyzer. This method calls the callback parameter only once, with as single parameter
 28          * an array of normalized words.
 29          * @param text some text to analyze
 30          * @param callback a function called with an array (possibly empty) of string
 31          */
 32         this.getArray = function(text, callback) {
 33             var parser_synchro = fullproof.make_synchro_point(function(array_of_words) {
 34                 callback(array_of_words);
 35             });
 36             this.parse(text, parser_synchro);
 37         };
 38 
 39     };
 40 
 41 	/**
 42 	 * A simple private parser that relies on the unicode letter/number
 43 	 * categories. Word boundaries are whatever is not a letter 
 44 	 * or a number.
 45 	 */
 46 	var simple_parser = function(str, callback, functor) {
 47 		functor = functor||net.kornr.unicode.is_letter_number;
 48 		var current_word = "";
 49 		for (var i=0,max=str.length; i<max; ++i) {
 50 			if (functor(str.charCodeAt(i))) {
 51 				current_word += str[i];
 52 			} else {
 53 				if (current_word.length>0) {
 54 					callback(current_word);
 55 					current_word = "";
 56 				}
 57 			}
 58 		}
 59 		if (current_word.length>0) {
 60 			callback(current_word);
 61 		}
 62 		callback(false);
 63 	};
 64 	
 65 	function arguments_to_array(args) {
 66 		var result = [];
 67 		for (var i=0; i<args.length; ++i) {
 68 			if (args[i].constructor == Array) {
 69 				result = result.concat(args[i]);
 70 			} else {
 71 				result.push(args[i]);
 72 			}
 73 		}
 74 		return result;
 75 	}
 76 	
 77 	/**
 78 	 * An analyzer with a parse() method. An analyzer does more than
 79 	 * just parse, as it normalizes each word calling the sequence
 80 	 * of normalizers specified when calling the constructor.
 81 	 * 
 82 	 * @constructor
 83 	 * @param normalizers... the constructor can take normalizers as parameters. Each 
 84 	 * normalizer is applied sequentially in the same order as they are
 85 	 * passed in the constructor.
 86 	 */
 87 	fullproof.StandardAnalyzer = function() {
 88         var normalizers = arguments_to_array(arguments);
 89 
 90         // Enforces new object
 91 		if (!(this instanceof fullproof.StandardAnalyzer)) {
 92 			return new fullproof.StandardAnalyzer(normalizers);
 93 		}
 94 
 95 		// Stores the normalizers... (don't store arguments, as it contains more than an array) 
 96 		this.provideScore = false;
 97 		/**
 98 		 * When true, the parser calls its callback function with 
 99 		 * the parameter {boolean}false when complete. This allows
100 		 * the callback to know when the parsing is complete. When
101 		 * this property is set to false, the parser never triggers
102 		 * the last call to callback(false).
103 		 * 
104 		 * @expose
105 		 */
106 		this.sendFalseWhenComplete = true;
107 		
108 		/**
109          * The main method: cuts the text in words, calls the normalizers on each word,
110          * then calls the callback with each non empty word.
111          * @param text the text to analyze
112          * @param callback a function called with each word found in the text.
113          */
114         this.parse = function (text, callback) {
115             var self = this;
116             simple_parser(text, function (word) {
117                 if (typeof word == "string") {
118                     word = word.trim();
119                     if (word != "") {
120                         for (var i = 0; i < normalizers.length; ++i) {
121                             word = normalizers[i](word);
122                         }
123                     }
124 
125                     if (callback && word && word != "") {
126                         callback(word);
127                     }
128                 } else if (word === false && self.sendFalseWhenComplete && callback) {
129                     callback(word);
130                 }
131             });
132         };
133 	};
134 
135     fullproof.StandardAnalyzer.prototype = new fullproof.AbstractAnalyzer();
136 
137     /**
138      * The ScoringAnalyzer is not unlike the StandardAnalyzer, except that is attaches a score to each token,
139      * related to its place in the text. This is a very naive implementation, and therefore the adjustement
140      * is tweaked to be very light: it simplistically says that the more a token is near the start of the text,
141      * the more relevant it is to the document. Although very simple, it follows the normally expected form
142      * of a text where the headers and titles come first, and should provide decent result. You can use
143      * this as a basis and make a ScoringAnalyzer adapted to your data.
144      * @constructor
145      */
146 	fullproof.ScoringAnalyzer = function() {
147 		// Stores the normalizers... (don't store arguments, as it contains more than an array) 
148 		var normalizers = arguments_to_array(arguments);
149 		var analyzer = new fullproof.StandardAnalyzer(normalizers);
150 		this.sendFalseWhenComplete = analyzer.sendFalseWhenComplete = true;
151 		this.provideScore = true;
152 		
153 		this.parse = function (text, callback) {
154             var words = {};
155             var wordcount = 0;
156             var totalwc = 0;
157             var self = this;
158             analyzer.parse(text, function (word) {
159                 if (word !== false) {
160                     if (words[word] === undefined || words[word].constructor !== Array) {
161                         words[word] = [];
162                     }
163                     words[word].push(wordcount);
164                     totalwc += ++wordcount;
165                 } else {
166                     // Evaluate the score for each word
167                     for (var w in words) {
168                         var res = words[w];
169                         var offsetcount = 1;
170                         var occboost = 0;
171                         for (var i = 0; i < res.length; ++i) {
172                             occboost += (3.1415 - Math.log(1 + res[i])) / 10;
173                         }
174                         var countboost = Math.abs(Math.log(1 + res.length)) / 10;
175                         var score = 1 + occboost * 1.5 + countboost * 3;
176                         // console.log(w + ": " + words[w].join(",") + ", countboost: " + countboost + ", occboost: " + occboost);
177                         callback(new fullproof.ScoredEntry(w, undefined, score));
178                     }
179 
180                     if (self.sendFalseWhenComplete == true) {
181                         callback(false);
182                     }
183 
184                 }
185             });
186         };
187 		
188 
189 	};
190     fullproof.ScoringAnalyzer.prototype = new fullproof.AbstractAnalyzer();
191

212 /**
213  * A boolean-set based engine.
214  *
215  * @constructor
216  */
217 fullproof.BooleanEngine = function (storeDescriptors) {
218 
219     if (!(this instanceof fullproof.BooleanEngine)) {
220         return new fullproof.BooleanEngine(storeDescriptors);
221     }
222 
223     this.initAbstractEngine(storeDescriptors); // Init from the prototype
224 
225     /**
226      * The working mode when gathering result sets. There's no really any good reason to change this,
227      * but whatever, you can if you want.
228      */
229     this.booleanMode = fullproof.BooleanEngine.CONST_MODE_INTERSECT;
230 
231     /**
232      * Gather results for a query
233      * @param self the BooleanEngine instance it works with
234      * @param text the text query too look up in the indexes
235      * @param callback a function called when some results are found. Receives an argument: false if failed to get any result, or a resultset if some documents were found.
236      * @param arrayOfIndexUnits a mutable array of IndexUnits that is recursively consumed, and that contains references to the indexes to use.
237      * @param mode The search mode, normally this should be self.booleanMode
238      * @private
239      */
240     function lookup(self, text, callback, arrayOfIndexUnits, mode) {
241         if (arrayOfIndexUnits.length == 0) {
242             return callback(false);
243         }
244         var unit = arrayOfIndexUnits.shift();
245         ++(self.lastResultIndex);
246         unit.analyzer.parse(text, fullproof.make_synchro_point(function (array_of_words) {
247 
248             if (!array_of_words || array_of_words.length == 0) {
249                 if (arrayOfIndexUnits.length > 0) {
250                     return lookup(self, text, callback, arrayOfIndexUnits, mode);
251                 } else {
252                     return callback(false);
253                 }
254             }
255 
256             var lookup_synchro = fullproof.make_synchro_point(function (rset_array) {
257 
258                 var curset = rset_array.shift();
259                 while (rset_array.length > 0) {
260                     var set = rset_array.shift();
261                     switch (mode) {
262                         case fullproof.BooleanEngine.CONST_MODE_UNION:
263                             curset.merge(set);
264                             break;
265                         default: // default is intersect
266                             curset.intersect(set);
267                             break;
268                     }
269                 }
270 
271                 if (curset.getSize() == 0) {
272                     if (arrayOfIndexUnits.length > 0) {
273                         return lookup(self, text, callback, arrayOfIndexUnits, mode);
274                     } else {
275                         callback(false);
276                     }
277                 } else {
278                     callback(curset);
279                 }
280 
281             }, array_of_words.length);
282 
283             for (var i = 0; i < array_of_words.length; ++i) {
284                 unit.index.lookup(array_of_words[i], lookup_synchro);
285             }
286         }));
287     }
288 
289     /**
290      * Looks up in the indexes for the query.
291      * @param text the query text to look up
292      * @param callback function called when the lookup is complete. It is passed false if nothing was found, or a ResultSet otherwise.
293      */
294     this.lookup = function (text, callback) {
295         this.lastResultIndex = 0;
296         lookup(this, text, callback, this.getIndexUnits(), this.booleanMode);
297         return this;
298     }
299 };

329 /**
330  * Represents a set of contraints applied to an index or a store.
331  * The way this object is designed, you only have to set the properties that are meaningful for your
332  * requirement. Not setting a property means that any value is ok.
333  * @constructor
334  */
335 fullproof.Capabilities = function() {
336 	if (!(this instanceof fullproof.Capabilities)) {
337 		return new fullproof.Capabilities();
338 	}

341 /**
342  * Compares a value with a property of this Capabilities object.
343  * @param property a property name
344  * @param value the valued to be compared
345  * @protected
346  * This should probably be made private or something
347  */
348 fullproof.Capabilities.prototype.matchValue = function (property, value) {
349     if (value === undefined) {
350         return true;
351     } else if (typeof property == "object" && property.constructor == Array) {
352         for (var i = 0; i < property.length; ++i) {
353             if (property[i] === value) {
354                 return true;
355             }
356         }
357         return false;
358     } else {
359         return property === value;
360     }
361 };

454 /**
455  * Returns true if the current Capabilities object subsumes another Capabilities.
456  * @param otherCapabilities the Capabilities that must be subsumed by the current instance
457  */
458 fullproof.Capabilities.prototype.isCompatibleWith = function (otherCapabilities) {
459     var objstore = this.matchValue(this.canStoreObjects, otherCapabilities.canStoreObjects);
460     var isvol = this.matchValue(this.isVolatile, otherCapabilities.isVolatile);
461     var score = this.matchValue(this.useScores, otherCapabilities.useScores);
462     var isavail = this.isAvailable === true;
463 
464     return objstore && isvol && isavail && score;
465 };

484 /**
485  * A TextInjector associates an index and an analyzer to provide an
486  * object able to inject texts.
487  * 
488  * @constructor
489  * @param index the index to use when injecting
490  * @param analyzer the analyzer to use to parse and normalize the text
491  * TODO: move this object in its own place or in utils
492  */
493 fullproof.TextInjector = function(index, analyzer) {
494 	if (!(this instanceof fullproof.TextInjector)) {
495 		return new fullproof.TextInjector(index,analyzer);
496 	}
497 	this.index = index;
498 	this.analyzer = analyzer;
499 };
500 
501 /**
502  * Inject a text and associates each of the word it composed with the provided value.
503  * @param text some text to inject in the index
504  * @param value the value associated to each word from the text
505  * @param callback a function to call when the injection is complete
506  */
507 fullproof.TextInjector.prototype.inject = function(text,value,callback) {
508 	var self = this;
509 	this.analyzer.getArray(text, function(array_of_words) {
510 		var synchro = fullproof.make_synchro_point(callback, array_of_words.length);
511 		for (var i=0; i<array_of_words.length; ++i) {
512 			var val = array_of_words[i];
513 			if (val instanceof fullproof.ScoredEntry) {
514 				val.value = val.value===undefined?value:val.value;
515 				self.index.inject(val.key, val, synchro); // the line number is the value stored
516 			} else {
517 				self.index.inject(array_of_words[i], value, synchro); // the line number is the value stored
518 			}
519 		}
520 	});
521 };

523 /**
524  * Bulk-inject an array of  text and an array of values. The text injected is associated to the value
525  * of the same index from the valueArray array. An optional progress function is called at regular interval
526  * to provide a way for the caller to give user feedback on the process.
527  * 
528  * @param texArray an array of text
529  * @param valueArray an array of values. The length of valueArray must equal the length of textArray.
530  * @param callback a function to call when the injection is complete
531  * @param progressCallback a function called with progress indication. A numeric argument is provided to 
532  * the function, which ranges from 0 to 1 (0 meaning not done, 1 meaning complete). Note that due to the
533  * floating nature of numeric values in javascript, you should not rely on receiving a 1, rather use
534  * the callback function parameter, which will be always called on completion of the injection.
535  */
536 fullproof.TextInjector.prototype.injectBulk = function(textArray, valueArray, callback, progressCallback) {
537 	var words = [];
538 	var values = [];
539 	var self = this;
540 	for (var i=0, max=Math.min(textArray.length, valueArray.length); i<max; ++i) {
541 		(function(text,value) {
542 			self.analyzer.getArray(text, function(array_of_words) {
543 				for (var w=0; w<array_of_words.length; ++w) {
544 					var val = array_of_words[w];
545 					if (val instanceof fullproof.ScoredEntry) {
546 						val.value = val.value===undefined?value:val.value;
547 						words.push(val.key);
548 						values.push(val);
549 					} else {
550 						words.push(val);
551 						values.push(value);
552 					}
553 				}
554 			});
555 		})(textArray[i], valueArray[i]);
556 	}
557 	this.index.injectBulk(words,values, callback, progressCallback);
558 };

595 fullproof.AbstractEngine.prototype.checkCapabilities = function (capabilities, analyzer) {
596     return true;

599 /**
600  * Adds an array of index units
601  * @param indexes an array of fullproof.IndexUnit instances
602  * @param callback the function to call when all the indexes are added
603  * @private
604  * @static
605  */
606 fullproof.AbstractEngine.addIndexes = function (engine, indexes, callback) {
607     var starter = false;
608     while (indexes.length > 0) {
609         var data = indexes.pop();
610         starter = (function (next, data) {
611             return function () {
612                 fullproof.AbstractEngine.addIndex(engine, data.name, data.analyzer, data.capabilities, data.initializer, next !== false ? next : callback);
613             };
614         })(starter, data);
615     }
616     if (starter !== false) {
617         starter();
618     }
619     return this;
620 };

622 /**
623  * Adds un index to the engine. It is not possible to add an index after the engine was opened.
624  * @param name the name of the engine
625  * @param the analyzer used to parse the text
626  * @param capabilities a fullproof.Capabilities instance describing the requirements for the index
627  * @param initializer a function called when the index is created. This function can be used to populate the index.
628  * @param completionCallback a function on completion, with true if the index was successfully added, false otherwise.
629  * @return this instance
630  * @private
631  * @static
632  */
633 fullproof.AbstractEngine.addIndex = function(engine, name, analyzer, capabilities, initializer, completionCallback) {
634 	var self = engine;
635 	var indexData = new fullproof.IndexUnit(name,capabilities,analyzer); 
636 
637 	if (!engine.checkCapabilities(capabilities, analyzer)) {
638 		return completionCallback(false);
639 	}
640 
641 	var indexRequest = new fullproof.IndexRequest(name, capabilities, function(index, callback) {
642 		var injector = new fullproof.TextInjector(index, indexData.analyzer);
643 		initializer(injector, callback);
644 	});
645 	
646 	if (engine.storeManager.addIndex(indexRequest)) {
647 		if (engine.indexes === undefined) {
648             engine.indexes = [];
649 		}
650         engine.indexes.push(indexData);
651         engine.indexesByName[name] = indexData;
652 		if (completionCallback) {
653 			completionCallback(true);
654 		}
655 		return true;
656 	} else {
657 		if (completionCallback) {
658 			completionCallback(false);
659 		}
660 		return false;
661 	}
662 };

664 /**
665  * Opens the engine: this function opens all the indexes at once, makes the initialization if needed,
666  *  and makes this engine ready for use. Do not use any function of an engine, except addIndex, before
667  *  having opened it.
668  *  @param indexArray an array of index descriptors. Each descriptor is an object that defines the name, analyzer, capabilities, and initializer properties.
669  *  @param callback function called when the engine is properly opened
670  *  @param errorCallback function called if for some reason the engine cannot open some index
671  */
672 fullproof.AbstractEngine.prototype.open = function (indexArray, callback, errorCallback) {
673     var self = this;
674     indexArray = (indexArray.constructor !== Array)?[indexArray]:indexArray; // Makes it an Array if it's not
675     fullproof.AbstractEngine.addIndexes(self, indexArray);
676 
677     this.storeManager.openIndexes(function (storesArray) {
678         self.storeManager.forEach(function (name, index) {
679             self.indexesByName[name].index = index;
680         });
681         callback(self);
682     }, errorCallback);
683     return this;
684 };

686 /**
687  * Inject a text document into all the indexes managed by the engine.
688  * @param text some text to be parsed and indexed
689  * @param value the primary value (number or string) associated to this object.
690  * @param callback the function called when the text injection is done
691  */
692 fullproof.AbstractEngine.prototype.injectDocument = function(text, value, callback) {
693 	var synchro = fullproof.make_synchro_point(function(data) {
694 		callback();
695 	});
696 
697 	this.forEach(function(name, index, parser) {
698 		if (name) {
699 			parser.parse(text, function(word) {
700 				if (word) {
701 					index.inject(word, value, synchro); // the line number is the value stored
702 				} else {
703 					synchro(false);

717     "use strict";

719         return callback();

807 /**
808  * Converts a word into a canonical Unicode decomposed and lowercased form.
809  * @param word a token to transform
810  * @param callback a function called with the converted word (optional)
811  * @return the result of the callback function, or the converted word is there is no callback.
812  */
813 fullproof.normalizer.to_lowercase_decomp = function(word, callback) {
814     word = word?net.kornr.unicode.lowercase(word):word;
815     return callback?callback(word):word;
816 };

819  * Convertes a word to lowercase and remove all its diacritical marks.
820  * @param word a token to transform
821  * @param callback a function called with the converted word (optional)
822  * @return the result of the callback function, or the converted word is there is no callback.
823  */
824 fullproof.normalizer.to_lowercase_nomark = function(word, callback) {
825     word = word?net.kornr.unicode.lowercase_nomark(word):word;
826     return callback?callback(word):word;

829 /**
830  * Remove all the duplicate letters in a word. For instance TESSTT is converted to TEST, CHEESE is converted to CHESE.
831  * @param word a token to transform
832  * @param callback a function called with the converted word (optional)
833  * @return the result of the callback function, or the converted word is there is no callback.
834  */
835 fullproof.normalizer.remove_duplicate_letters = function(word, callback) {
836     var res = word?"":false;
837     var last = false;
838     if (word) {
839         for (var i=0,max=word.length; i<max; ++i) {
840             if (last) {
841                 if (last != word[i]) {
842                     res +=last;
843                 }
844             }
845             last = word[i];
846         }
847         res += last?last:"";
848     }
849     return callback?callback(res):res;
850 };

855  * @param array

859 fullproof.normalizer.filter_in_object = function(word, array, callback) {
860     if (array[word]) {
861         return callback?callback(false):false;
862     }
863     return callback?callback(word):word;

887 		lower_than: function(a,b) {
888 			return a<b;

896 	/**
897      * Binary search an array.
898      * @param array an array to search in
899      * @param value the value to search for
900      * @param min the floor index
901      * @param max the ceil index
902      * @param lower_than an optional function that takes two arguments and returns true if
903      * the first argument is lower than the second one. You have to provide this function
904      * if the values stored in the array cannot be sorted by the default javascript < operator.
905      *
906      * @return the index of the value, if found, or the index where the value can be inserted if not found.
907      */
908     fullproof.binary_search = function (array, value, min, max, lower_than) {
909         lower_than = lower_than || defaultComparator.lower_than;
910         if (min === undefined && max === undefined) {
911             if (array.length == 0) {
912                 return 0
913             } else {
914                 return fullproof.binary_search(array, value, 0, array.length, lower_than);
915             }
916         }
917 
918         while (max >= min) {
919             var mid = parseInt((max + min) / 2);
920             if (mid >= array.length) {
921                 return array.length;
922             } else if (lower_than(array[mid], value)) {
923                 min = mid + 1;
924             } else if (lower_than(value, array[mid])) {
925                 max = mid - 1;
926             } else {
927                 // Found
928                 return mid;
929             }
930         }
931         // Not found
932         return min;
933     };

935 	/**
936 	 *  Provides an object containing a sorted array, and providing elementary
937 	 *  set operations: merge (union), intersect, and substract (complement).
938 	 *  It maintains internally a sorted array of data. The optional comparator
939 	 *  must be an object of the form {lower_than: func_lt, equals: func_equal}
940 	 *  
941 	 *  @constructor
942 	 *  @param comparatorObject a comparator object that provides two functions: lower_than and equals.
943 	 *  If not defined, a default comparator using the javascript < operator is used. If you're only 
944 	 *  storing integer values, you can safely omit this argument.
945 	 */
946 	fullproof.ResultSet = function(comparatorObject, data) {
947 		if (!(this instanceof fullproof.ResultSet)) {
948 			return new fullproof.ResultSet(comparatorObject,data);
949 		}
950 		this.comparatorObject = comparatorObject||defaultComparator;
951 		this.data = data||[];
952 		this.last_insert = undefined;
953 	};

955 	/**
956 	 * Insert values into the array of data managed by this ResultSet. The insertion is optimized 
957 	 * when the inserted values are greater than the last inserted values (the value is just pushed
958 	 * to the end of the array). Otherwise, a binary search is done in the array to find the correct
959 	 * offset where to insert the value. When possible, always insert sorted data.
960 	 * 
961 	 * @param values... any number of values to insert in this resultset.
962 	 */
963 	fullproof.ResultSet.prototype.insert = function() {
964 		for (var i=0; i<arguments.length; ++i) {
965 			var obj = arguments[i];
966 			
967 			if (this.last_insert && this.comparatorObject.lower_than(this.last_insert,obj)) {
968 				this.data.push(obj);
969 				this.last_insert = obj
970 			} else {
971 				var index = fullproof.binary_search(this.data, obj, undefined, undefined, this.comparatorObject.lower_than);
972 				if (index >= this.data.length) {
973 					this.data.push(obj);
974 					this.last_insert = obj
975 				} else if (this.comparatorObject.equals(obj, this.data[index]) == false) {
976 					this.data.splice(index, 0, arguments[i]);
977 					this.last_insert = undefined;
978 				}
979 			}
980 		}
981 		return this;
982 	};

984 	function defaultMergeFn(a,b) {
985 		return a;

988 	/**
989      * Union operation. Merge another ResultSet or a sorted javascript array into this ResultSet.
990      * If the same value exists in both sets, it is not injected in the current set, to avoid duplicate values.
991      * @param set another ResultSet, or an array of sorted values
992      * @return this ResultSet, possibly modified by the merge operation
993      */
994     fullproof.ResultSet.prototype.merge = function (set, mergeFn) {
995         mergeFn = mergeFn || defaultMergeFn;
996         this.last_insert = undefined;
997         var other = false;
998 
999         if (set.constructor == Array) {
1000             other = set;
1001         } else if (set instanceof fullproof.ResultSet) {
1002             other = set.getDataUnsafe();
1003         }
1004 
1005 
1006         var i1 = 0, max1 = this.data.length,
1007             i2 = 0, max2 = other.length,
1008             obj1 = null, obj2 = null;
1009         var comp = this.comparatorObject;
1010 
1011         var result = [];
1012         while (i1 < max1 && i2 < max2) {
1013             obj1 = this.data[i1];
1014             obj2 = other[i2];
1015             if (comp.equals(obj1, obj2)) {
1016                 result.push(mergeFn(obj1, obj2));
1017                 ++i1;
1018                 ++i2;
1019             } else if (comp.lower_than(obj1, obj2)) {
1020                 result.push(obj1);
1021                 ++i1;
1022             } else {
1023                 result.push(obj2);
1024                 ++i2;
1025             }
1026         }
1027         while (i1 < max1) {
1028             result.push(this.data[i1]);
1029             ++i1;
1030         }
1031         while (i2 < max2) {
1032             result.push(other[i2]);
1033             ++i2;
1034         }
1035         this.data = result;
1036         return this;
1037     };

1040 	/**
1041      * Intersect operation. Modify the current ResultSet so that is only contain values that are also contained by another ResultSet or array.
1042      * @param set another ResultSet, or an array of sorted values
1043      * @return this ResultSet, possibly modified by the intersect operation
1044      */
1045     fullproof.ResultSet.prototype.intersect = function (set) {
1046         this.last_insert = undefined;
1047         var other = false;
1048         if (set.constructor == Array) {
1049             other = set;
1050         } else if (set instanceof fullproof.ResultSet) {
1051             other = set.getDataUnsafe();
1052         }
1053 
1054         if (other) {
1055             var result = [];
1056             var i = 0, j = 0, maxi = this.data.length, maxj = other.length;
1057             while (i < maxi) {
1058                 while (j < maxj && this.comparatorObject.lower_than(other[j], this.data[i])) {
1059                     ++j;
1060                 }
1061                 if (j < maxj && this.comparatorObject.equals(other[j], this.data[i])) {
1062                     result.push(other[j]);
1063                     ++i;
1064                     ++j;
1065                 } else {
1066                     i++;
1067                 }
1068             }
1069             this.data = result;
1070         } else {
1071             this.data = [];
1072         }
1073         return this;
1074     };

1078 	 * Substraction operation. Modify the current ResultSet so that any value contained in the provided set of values are removed.
1079 	 * @param set another ResultSet, or an array of sorted values
1080 	 * @return this ResultSet, possibly modified by the substract operation
1081 	 */
1082 	fullproof.ResultSet.prototype.substract = function(set) {
1083 		this.last_insert = undefined;
1084 		var other = false;
1085 		if (set.constructor == Array) {
1086 			other = set;
1087 		} else if (set instanceof fullproof.ResultSet) {
1088 			other = set.getDataUnsafe();

1090

1094 			while (i<maxi) {
1095 				while (j<maxj && this.comparatorObject.lower_than(other[j],this.data[i])) {
1096 					++j;
1097 				}
1098 				if (j<maxj && this.comparatorObject.equals(other[j],this.data[i])) {
1099 					++i; 
1100 					++j;
1101 				} else {
1102 					result.push(this.data[i]);
1103 					i++;
1104 				}
1105 			}
1106 			this.data = result;
1107 		} else {
1108 			this.data = [];
1109 		}
1110 		
1111 		return this;

1360 			return false;

1363 			if (pool[i].ref.getCapabilities().isCompatibleWith(requiredCaps)) {
1364 				return pool[i];

1535 /**
1536  * Creates a synchronization point. This function returns a function that collects
1537  * calls to callback, then calls its callback argument with all the data collected.
1538  * The synchronization point can trigger the final call to callback when it either
1539  * receives a fixed number of calls (expected argument >= 1), or when it
1540  * receives a false boolean value as argument (expected has to be either undefined or false)
1541 
1542  * @param {function} callback the function to call when the synchronization point is reached
1543  * @param {number} expected defines the synchronization point. If this is a number, the synchronization is
1544  * triggered when the function returned is called this number of times. If this is set undefined, the sync is
1545  * triggered when this function returned is called with a single argument {boolean} false.
1546  * @param debug if defined, some debugging information are printed to the console, if it exists.
1547  */
1548 fullproof.make_synchro_point = function (callback, expected, debug, thrown_if_false) {
1549     var count = 0;
1550     var results = [];
1551     return function (res) {
1552         if (thrown_if_false !== undefined && res === false) {
1553             throw thrown_if_false;
1554         }
1555         if (expected === false || expected === undefined) {
1556             if (res === false) {
1557                 callback(results);
1558             } else {
1559                 results.push(res);
1560             }
1561         } else {
1562 
1563             ++count;
1564             results.push(res);
1565             if (debug && console && console.log) {
1566                 console.log("synchro point " + (typeof debug == "string" ? debug + ": " : ": ") + count + " / " + expected);
1567             }
1568             if (count == expected) {
1569                 callback(results);
1570             }
1571         }
1572     }
1573 };

1580 			func.apply(this, args);
1581 		}
1582 	}, 1);
1583 };

2638
